    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offering a concours-level 2004 Honda S2000 AP2, an exquisite example of high-revving naturally aspirated engineering. This specimen features the F22C1 longitudinal inline-four, delivering a linear power band and a visceral 8,200 RPM redline. The chassis retains its factory-spec rigidity via the signature X-bone frame and double-wishbone suspension at all four corners, ensuring surgical turn-in and neutral handling characteristics. The close-ratio six-speed manual transmission provides tactile, short-throw shifts, synchronizing perfectly with the factory Torsen helical limited-slip differential. This unit is mechanically flawless with a documented service history, showcasing zero bolster wear and a pristine undercarriage. A collector-grade masterpiece for the purist seeking a raw, analog driving experience.",
